  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Orion Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project comprises the construction of a greenfield bleached eucalyptus kraft pulp (BEKP) mill with annual capacity of one million tons in Fray Bentos (Uruguay) by Europes second largest pulp producer, OY Metsa Botnia AB (Botnia, or the sponsor) from Finland.  Uruguay is one of very few locations in the world where already existing plantations can supply the raw material for a new pulp mill of this scale.  Wood for the mill will be procured from existing plantations owned by the sponsors and from third parties within Uruguay and Argentina.</narrative>
  </description>
